sauté the pieces on one side for three minutes, then turn them over to sauté the other side. Cook them long enough to impart their flavor to the base, but not so long that they're entirely cooked through. Stir the squid to keep the pieces from sticking to the bottom of the pan. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b9/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b9/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/aid1968991-v4-728px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add a little more oil to the pan if the squid starts to stick before it's finished sauteing. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/92/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/92/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/aid1968991-v4-728px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add three cups of the stock, the red pepper flakes, salt, and black pepper. Use a wooden spoon or spatula to loosen the frying onions and peppers and stir the mixture together. Turn up the heat to bring it to a boil, then reduce it to a simmer and let the paella cook. Do not stir the rice and other ingredients after you pour in the broth. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/99/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/99/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/aid1968991-v4-728px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

As the rice cooks and absorbs the broth, slowly add more broth 1/2 cup at a time. Continue adding broth until the rice is completely cooked. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/3/38/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/aid1968991-v4-728px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

The lobster and mussels will cook in the hot paella once it is covered. Let the seafood steam for 10 minutes. Remove the cover and check to make sure the seafood is completely cooked. The lobster meat should be opaque and tender when it's finished cooking. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f6/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/f/f6/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/aid1968991-v4-728px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

The mussel shells should be open; if you think the dish is finished cooking, but some mussels remain closed, discard them. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/57/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/57/Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/aid1968991-v4-728px-Cook-Seafood-Paella-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
